{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"mutating"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"partition"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"by"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"belongsInSecondPartition"},{"kind":"text","text":": ("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/BidirectionalCollection/Element","preciseIdentifier":"s:SK7ElementQa","text":"Element"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"rethrows"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/BidirectionalCollection/Index","preciseIdentifier":"s:SK5IndexQa","text":"Index"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"belongsInSecondPartition","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A predicate used to partition"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the collection. All elements satisfying this predicate are ordered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"after all elements not satisfying it."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"return-value","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Return Value"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The index of the first element in the reordered collection"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that matches "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"belongsInSecondPartition"},{"type":"text","text":". If no elements in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"collection match "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"belongsInSecondPartition"},{"type":"text","text":", the returned index is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"equal to the collection’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"endIndex"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After partitioning a collection, there is a pivot index "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"type":"text","text":" where"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"no element before "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"type":"text","text":" satisfies the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"belongsInSecondPartition"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"predicate and every element at or after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"type":"text","text":" satisfies"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"belongsInSecondPartition"},{"type":"text","text":". This operation isn’t guaranteed to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stable, so the relative ordering of elements within the partitions might"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"change."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the following example, an array of numbers is partitioned by a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"predicate that matches elements greater than 30."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["var numbers = [30, 40, 20, 30, 30, 60, 10]","let p = numbers.partition(by: { $0 > 30 })","// p == 5","// numbers == [30, 10, 20, 30, 30, 60, 40]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numbers"},{"type":"text","text":" array is now arranged in two partitions. The first"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"partition, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numbers[..<p]"},{"type":"text","text":", is made up of the elements that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are not greater than 30. The second partition, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numbers[p...]"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is made up of the elements that "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"are"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" greater than 30."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let first = numbers[..<p]","// first == [30, 10, 20, 30, 30]","let second = numbers[p...]","// second == [60, 40]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the order of elements in both partitions changed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"That is, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"40"},{"type":"text","text":" appears before "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"60"},{"type":"text","text":" in the original collection,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but, after calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partition(by:)"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"60"},{"type":"text","text":" appears before "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"40"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Complexity","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"O("},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}]},{"type":"text","text":"), where "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is the length of the collection."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/swift/array/partition(by:)-33stm"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Reorders the elements of the collection such that all the elements"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that match the given predicate are after all the elements that don’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"match."}],"metadata":{"conformance":{"availabilityPrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Available when"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Conforms when"}],"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Self"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"BidirectionalCollection"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"Swift","title":"partition(by:)","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"externalID":"s:SMsSKRzrlE9partition2by5IndexSlQzSb7ElementSTQzKXE_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:Sa","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"partition"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"by"},{"kind":"text","text":": ("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Element","preciseIdentifier":"s:SK7ElementQa"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"rethrows"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Index","preciseIdentifier":"s:SK5IndexQa"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Array"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Array/partition(by:)-33stm"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/BidirectionalCollection/Index":{"url":"/documentation/swift/bidirectionalcollection/index","title":"Index","abstract":[],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"associatedtype"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Index"}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/BidirectionalCollection/Index","required":true,"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","type":"topic","url":"/documentation/swift","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Build apps using a powerful open language.","type":"text"}],"title":"Swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool","type":"topic","title":"Bool","kind":"symbol","url":"/documentation/swift/bool","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Bool"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Bool"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A value type whose instances are either ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Array/partition(by:)-33stm":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"partition"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"by"},{"kind":"text","text":": ("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SK7ElementQa","text":"Element"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"rethrows"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SK5IndexQa","text":"Index"}],"role":"symbol","url":"/documentation/swift/array/partition(by:)-33stm","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Reorders the elements of the collection such that all the elements"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that match the given predicate are after all the elements that don’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"match."}],"conformance":{"availabilityPrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Available when"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Conforms when"}],"constraints":[{"code":"Self","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"code":"BidirectionalCollection","